{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":4000,"text":"If you're at all like me,"},{"time":5000,"text":"this is what you do with the sunny summer weekends in San Francisco:"},{"time":8000,"text":"you build experimental kite-powered hydrofoils"},{"time":11000,"text":"capable of more than 30 knots."},{"time":13000,"text":"And you realize that there is incredible power in the wind,"},{"time":16000,"text":"and it can do amazing things."},{"time":18000,"text":"And one day, a vessel not unlike this"},{"time":20000,"text":"will probably break the world speed record."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22000,"text":"But kites aren't just toys like this."},{"time":25000,"text":"Kites: I'm going to give you a brief history,"},{"time":27000,"text":"and tell you about the magnificent future"},{"time":29000,"text":"of every child's favorite plaything."},{"time":32000,"text":"So, kites are more than a thousand years old,"},{"time":34000,"text":"and the Chinese used them for military applications,"},{"time":37000,"text":"and even for lifting men."},{"time":38000,"text":"So they knew at that stage they could carry large weights."},{"time":41000,"text":"I'm not sure why there is a hole in this particular man."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":45000,"text":"In 1827, a fellow called George Pocock"},{"time":48000,"text":"actually pioneered the use of kites for towing buggies"},{"time":51000,"text":"in races against horse carriages across the English countryside."},{"time":56000,"text":"Then of course, at the dawn of aviation,"},{"time":58000,"text":"all of the great inventors of the time --"},{"time":60000,"text":"like Hargreaves, like Langley,"},{"time":62000,"text":"even Alexander Graham Bell, inventor of the telephone, who was flying this kite --"},{"time":65000,"text":"were doing so in the pursuit of aviation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68000,"text":"Then these two fellows came along,"},{"time":70000,"text":"and they were flying kites to develop the control systems"},{"time":73000,"text":"that would ultimately enable powered human flight."},{"time":76000,"text":"So this is of course Orville and Wilbur Wright,"},{"time":79000,"text":"and the Wright Flyer."},{"time":81000,"text":"And their experiments with kites led to this"},{"time":83000,"text":"momentous occasion, where we powered up and took off for the"},{"time":86000,"text":"first-ever 12-second human flight."},{"time":90000,"text":"And that was fantastic for the future of commercial aviation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94000,"text":"But unfortunately, it relegated kites once again to be considered children's toys."},{"time":98000,"text":"That was until the 1970s, where we had the last energy crisis."},{"time":102000,"text":"And a fabulous man called Miles Loyd"},{"time":104000,"text":"who lives on the outskirts of San Francisco,"},{"time":106000,"text":"wrote this seminal paper that was completely ignored"},{"time":109000,"text":"in the Journal of Energy"},{"time":110000,"text":"about how to use basically an airplane on a piece of string"},{"time":114000,"text":"to generate enormous amounts of electricity."},{"time":117000,"text":"The real key observation he made is that"},{"time":119000,"text":"a free-flying wing can sweep through more sky and generate more power"},{"time":123000,"text":"in a unit of time than a fixed-wing turbine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127000,"text":"So turbines grew. And they can now span up to three hundred feet at the hub height,"},{"time":131000,"text":"but they can't really go a lot higher,"},{"time":133000,"text":"and more height is where the more wind is, and more power --"},{"time":136000,"text":"as much as twice as much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138000,"text":"So cut to now. We still have an energy crisis,"},{"time":141000,"text":"and now we have a climate crisis as well. You know,"},{"time":144000,"text":"so humans generate about 12 trillion watts,"},{"time":147000,"text":"or 12 terawatts, from fossil fuels."},{"time":149000,"text":"And Al Gore has spoken to why we need to hit one of these targets,"},{"time":153000,"text":"and in reality what that means is in the next 30 to 40 years,"},{"time":157000,"text":"we have to make 10 trillion watts or more of new clean energy somehow."},{"time":163000,"text":"Wind is the second-largest renewable resource after solar:"},{"time":167000,"text":"3600 terawatts, more than enough to supply humanity 200 times over."},{"time":171000,"text":"The majority of it is in the higher altitudes, above 300 feet,"},{"time":175000,"text":"where we don't have a technology as yet to get there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179000,"text":"So this is the dawn of the new age of kites."},{"time":181000,"text":"This is our test site on Maui, flying across the sky."},{"time":185000,"text":"I'm now going to show you"},{"time":187000,"text":"the first autonomous generation of power"},{"time":190000,"text":"by every child's favorite plaything."},{"time":193000,"text":"As you can tell, you need to be a robot to fly this thing for thousands of hours."},{"time":197000,"text":"It makes you a little nauseous."},{"time":199000,"text":"And here we're actually generating about 10 kilowatts --"},{"time":201000,"text":"so, enough to power probably five United States households --"},{"time":204000,"text":"with a kite not much larger than this piano."},{"time":207000,"text":"And the real significant thing here"},{"time":209000,"text":"is we're developing the control systems,"},{"time":211000,"text":"as did the Wright brothers, that would enable sustained, long-duration flight."},{"time":216000,"text":"And it doesn't hurt to do it in a location like this either."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221000,"text":"So this is the equivalent for a kite flier of peeing in the snow --"},{"time":224000,"text":"that's tracing your name in the sky."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226000,"text":"And this is where we're actually going."},{"time":228000,"text":"So we're beyond the 12-second steps."},{"time":230000,"text":"And we're working towards megawatt-scale machines"},{"time":232000,"text":"that fly at 2000 feet and generate tons of clean electricity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236000,"text":"So you ask, how big are those machines?"},{"time":238000,"text":"Well, this paper plane would be maybe a -- oop!"},{"time":241000,"text":"That would be enough to power your cell phone."},{"time":244000,"text":"Your Cessna would be 230 killowatts."},{"time":247000,"text":"If you'd loan me your Gulfstream, I'll rip its wings off and generate you a megawatt."},{"time":251000,"text":"If you give me a 747, I'll make six megawatts,"},{"time":254000,"text":"which is more than the largest wind turbines today."},{"time":257000,"text":"And the Spruce Goose would be a 15-megawatt wing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260000,"text":"So that is audacious, you say. I agree."},{"time":263000,"text":"But audacious is what has happened many times before in history."},{"time":266000,"text":"This is a refrigerator factory,"},{"time":268000,"text":"churning out airplanes for World War II."},{"time":271000,"text":"Prior to World War II, they were making 1000 planes a year."},{"time":274000,"text":"By 1945, they were making 100,000."},{"time":277000,"text":"With this factory and 100,000 planes a year,"},{"time":279000,"text":"we could make all of America's electricity in about 10 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283000,"text":"So really this is a story about the audacious plans of young people"},{"time":286000,"text":"with these dreams. There are many of us."},{"time":288000,"text":"I am lucky enough to work with 30 of them."},{"time":290000,"text":"And I think we need to support all of the dreams"},{"time":292000,"text":"of the kids out there doing these crazy things."},{"time":295000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":296000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}